{"title_page": "3MA (music group)", "text_new": "{{Infobox musical artist\n  | name        = 3MA\n  | image       = \n  | image_size     = \n  | caption      = \n  | background     = group_or_band\n  | birth_name     = \n  | alias       = \n  | birth_date     = \n  | birth_place    = \n  | origin          = \n  | instrument     = [[Kora (instrument)|kora]], [[oud]], [[valiha]]\n  | genre       = \n  | occupation     = \n  | years_active    = \n  | label       = \n  | associated_acts  = \n  | website      = \n  | notable_instruments= \n  | current_members = [[Ballak\u00e9 Sissoko]], Driss El Maloumi, [[Rajery]]\n  }}\n\n'''3MA''' is a music group consisting of members [[Ballak\u00e9 Sissoko]] from [[Mali]] on [[kora (instrument)|kora]], Driss El Maloumi from [[Morocco]] on [[Oud]] and [[Rajery]] from [[Madagascar]] on [[valiha]]. The band takes its name from the first two letters of each member's country of origin in French: '''Ma'''li, '''Ma'''roc, '''Ma'''dagascar.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sixdegreesrecords.com/3ma/|title=3MA (Ballak\u00e9 Sissoko, Driss El Maloumi, Rajery)|date=10 November 2017|website=Sixdegreesrecords.com|accessdate=27 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2008/jul/13/worldmusic.reviews|title=Review: Ballake Sissoko, Driss El Maloumi, Rajery - 3MA|first=Charlie|last=Gillett|date=12 July 2008|accessdate=27 March 2019|website=Theguardian.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://afropop.org/events/3ma-ballak\u00e9-sissoko-driss-el-maloumi-rajery|title=Afropop Worldwide - 3MA: Ballak\u00e9 Sissoko, Driss El Maloumi, Rajery|website=Afropop Worldwide|accessdate=27 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.songlines.co.uk/explore/features/3ma-african-chamber-music|title=3MA: African Chamber Music|website=Songlines.co.uk|accessdate=27 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kingsplace.co.uk/whats-on/world/3ma/|title=3MA \u2022 Kings Place|website=Kings Place|accessdate=27 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://worldmusiccentral.org/tag/3ma/|title=3MA - World Music Central.org|website=Worldmusiccentral.org|accessdate=27 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wearepublic.nl/en/event/ballake-sissoko-driss-el-maloumi-rajery-3ma/|title=Ballak\u00e9 Sissoko, Driss El Maloumi, Rajery - 3MA|website=Wearepublic.nl|accessdate=27 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n* ''3MA'' (2008)\n* ''Anarouz'' (2017)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:African musicians]]\n\n\n{{Africa-musician-stub}}\n{{band-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox musical artist\n  | name        = 3MA\n  | image       = \n  | image_size     = \n  | caption      = \n  | background     = group_or_band\n  | birth_name     = \n  | alias       = \n  | birth_date     = \n  | birth_place    = \n  | origin          = \n  | instrument     = [[Kora (instrument)|kora]], [[oud]], [[valiha]]\n  | genre       = \n  | occupation     = \n  | years_active    = \n  | label       = \n  | associated_acts  = \n  | website      = \n  | notable_instruments= \n  | current_members = [[Ballak\u00e9 Sissoko]], [[Driss El Maloumi]], [[Rajery]]\n  }}\n\n'''3MA''' is a music group consisting of members [[Ballak\u00e9 Sissoko]] from [[Mali]] on [[kora (instrument)|kora]], [[Driss El Maloumi]] from [[Morocco]] on [[Oud]] and [[Rajery]] from [[Madagascar]] on [[valiha]]. The band takes its name from the first two letters of each member's country of origin in French: '''Ma'''li, '''Ma'''roc, '''Ma'''dagascar.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sixdegreesrecords.com/3ma/|title=3MA (Ballak\u00e9 Sissoko, Driss El Maloumi, Rajery)|date=10 November 2017|website=Sixdegreesrecords.com|accessdate=27 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2008/jul/13/worldmusic.reviews|title=Review: Ballake Sissoko, Driss El Maloumi, Rajery - 3MA|first=Charlie|last=Gillett|date=12 July 2008|accessdate=27 March 2019|website=Theguardian.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://afropop.org/events/3ma-ballak\u0