web.archive.org/web/20100125113958/http://www.epo.gr/cup/09_10/program.asp?m_1=3 Greek Cup] at EPO.gr\n\n{{Greek Cup Seasons}}\n{{2009\u201310 in Greek football}}\n{{2009-10 in European Football (UEFA)}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Greek Cup 2009-10}}\n[[Category:Greek Football Cup seasons|2009-10]]\n[[Category:2009\u201310 in Greek football]]\n[[Category:2009\u201310 domestic association football cups]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football tournament season\n| title               = Greek Cup\n| year                = 2009\u201310\n| other_titles        =\n| image               =\n| imagesize           =\n| caption             =\n| country             = {{GRE}}\n| num_teams           = 70\n| defending champions = [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]]\n| champions           = [[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]] (17th title)\n| runner-up           = [[Aris Thessaloniki F.C.|Aris]]\n| matches             =\n| goals               =\n| top goal scorer     = Pavlos Leptokaridis <br> [[Benjamin Onwuachi]] <br> [[Koke (footballer)|Koke]] <br> (4 goals each)\n| prevseason          = [[2008\u201309 Greek Cup|2008\u201309]]\n| nextseason          = [[2010\u201311 Greek Cup|2010\u201311]]\n}}\nThe '''2009&ndash;10 [[Greek Cup]]''' was the 68th edition of the Greek Football Cup.\n\nThe competition culminated with the final held at [[Athens Olympic Stadium]] on 24 April 2010. [[Panathinaikos F.C|Panathinaikos]] earned the trophy with a 1-0<ref>{{cite web|title=\u03a0\u03b1\u03bd\u03b1\u03b8\u03b7\u03bd\u03b1\u03ca\u03ba\u03cc\u03c2-\u0391\u03c1\u03b7\u03c2 1-0|url=http://www.sport24.gr/football/omades/Aris/article368240.ece|language=Greek|work=sport24.gr|accessdate=6 June 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/memberassociations/news/newsid=1480868.html|title=Panathinaikos complete Greek double|work=uefa.com}}</ref> win over [[Aris Thessaloniki F.C|Aris]].\n\n==Calendar==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Round !! Date\n|- align=center\n| First Round || 22 & 23 August 2009\n|- align=center\